  "texts": [
    "As a result, metrics such as the velocity, runout height, overall landslide area, and volume constitute standard outputs of such a modeling approach (see, van den Bout et al., 2021b, a).",
    "However, these models are often constrained to single slopes or catchments because of the spatial data requirements on geotechnical parameters.",
    "This limitation has stimulated the geoscientific community Published by Copernicus Publications on behalf of the European Geosciences Union.",
    "to develop data-driven statistical models instead (Van Westen et al., 2006).",
    "These are much more versed in being extended over large regions because, rather than requiring specific geotechnical properties, they can rely on terrain attributes and remotely sensed data acting as geotechnical proxies (Van Westen et al., 2008; Frattini et al., 2010)."
  ],
